  <h2 class="entrydate">
    February 1, 2006  </h2>   <h3 class="entrytitle" id="post-124"> <a href="http://longorshortcapital.com/incredibly-true-quick-serve-restaurant-truths-2.htm" rel="bookmark">
    Incredibly True Quick Serve Restaurant Truths #2    </a> </h3>    


  <div class="entrybody">
    <p><a href="http://longorshortcapital.com/incredibly-true-quick-serve-restaurant-truths.htm">Cedric Burgher</a>, the most appropriately-named former CFO of Burger King, is now the CFO of KBR, the division of Halliburton (<a href="http://longorshortcapital.com/satans-portfolio.htm">HAL</a>) that does contingency support and various government subcontracting in Iraq and hotspots around the world.  Burgher moved from one about-to IPO company in <a href="http://biz.yahoo.com/ap/060201/burger_king_ipo.html?.v=9" class="broken_link">Burger King</a>, to another in KBR.</p>
<p>This is one of the worst things to ever happen and we fully hope that Burger King will scour finance departments nationwide until they can secure a new Hamburger Helper substitute CFO. This &#8220;John Chidsey&#8221; guy will not cut it&#8230;unless he changes his name to Stanley Chicken Frye.  Perhaps BK will just cut through the funny business and elevate The King from his SVP of Accounting role to CFO.</p>
